  "body": "```\r\nAs a developer\r\nI want to run tests in watch mode\r\nSo that I can make changes and check the tests without having to manually run them\r\n\r\nAs a developer\r\nI want to run only a subset of tests\r\nSo that I can quickly check that the test I am working on passes\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWe want to be able to run a script, that watches the cljs tests and re run them whenever any of the`cljs` files changes. \r\nWe would also like to be able to run a subset of tests (by regex, or by namespace for example, either is fine). \r\n\r\nSome documentation in`doc/` should also come with the PR, so other devs know how to run it.\r\n\r\nThese tests are currently run with `make test` ",
